      "content": "hey i'm working on this medical NLP thing and i need a quick python function for a dependency parser. i dont need it to be super complex yet, just something that takes a sentence and returns the head-child relationships as a list of tuples like (head, child). \n\nhere is the specific sentence and the structure i need it to match for my current test case:\n\nsentence: \"the patient shows signs of acute respiratory distress\"\nexpected_deps: [(\"shows\", \"patient\"), (\"shows\", \"signs\"), (\"signs\", \"of\"), (\"of\", \"distress\"), (\"distress\", \"respiratory\"), (\"respiratory\", \"acute\")]\n\ncan u write the function so it passes this? i'll be running it against a script later. thanks",
